<item>
            <title>[HBASE-3370] ReplicationSource.openReader fails to locate HLogs when they aren&apos;t split yet</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-3370</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In ReplicationSource.openReader there&apos;s a special handling of HLogs location during a failover and it&apos;s currently broken as it will retry 10 times and if the log splitting isn&apos;t done by then then it will skip the file forever.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;First issue is that it looks at the chain of failovers but not the oldest one.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Second issue is that the location is found starting from the current RS&apos;s folder, instead of the dead RS&apos;s folder.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
